n=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 5\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 6\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 7\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 8\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 9\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 10\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 11\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 12\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 13\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 14\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 15\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 16\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 17\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 18\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 19\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 20\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 21\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 22\n|-\n|[[File:BSicon LDER.svg|25px]] ||EOG\n||GEN||GEN||S9||S8||S7||S6||S5||S4||S3||S2||S1||PC||B4||B3||B2||B1||A1||H1||GEN||GEN||EOG\n|}\n\n==Journey==\nIt takes around 11 hours 55 minutes to cover its journey of {{convert|755|km|mi}} with an average speed of {{convert|63|kph|mph}}.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Patna Express]]\n* [[Neelachal Express]]\n* [[Kanpur Shatabdi]]\n* [[Gyan Ganga SF Express]]\n* [[Manduadih - New Delhi Superfast Express]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Railways in Northern India}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shiv Ganga Express}}\n[[Category:Named passenger trains of India]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Uttar Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Transport in Varanasi]]\n[[Category:Transport in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Express trains in India]]\n[[Category:Rail transport in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Railway services introduced in 2002]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2016}}\n{{ Infobox rail service\n| name= Shiv Ganga Express \u0936\u093f\u0935 \u0917\u0902\u0917\u093e \u090f\u0915\u094d\u0938\u092a\u094d\u0930\u0947\u0938\n| image= 12560 Shiv Ganga Express - Train board.jpg\n| caption= \n| type= [[Superfast/Mail Trains in India|Superfast]]\n| State= [[Delhi]], [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| first=1 July 2002\n| last=\n| operator=[[North Eastern Railway zone|North Eastern Railway]]\n| start= [[Manduadih railway station|Manduadih]]'''(MUV)'''\n| stops= 2\n| end=[[New Delhi Railway Station|New Delhi]]'''(NDLS)'''\n| distance= {{convert|755|km|miles}}\n| journeytime= 11 hours 55 minutes\n| frequency = Daily\n| class=  AC-I, AC-II, AC-III, SL, General\n| seating=Yes\n| sleeping=Yes\n| catering= Available (paid)\n| gauge= {{RailGauge|1676mm|lk=on|allk=on}}\n| trainnumber = 12559 / 12560\n| speed= Maximum {{convert|110|kph|mph}}\nAverage={{convert|63|kph|mph}} (inuding halts),\n{{convert|62|kph|mph}} (excluding halts)\n| map = [[File:Shiv Ganga Express (New Delhi - Varanasi) Route map.jpg|250px]]\n}}\n'''Shiv Ganga Express''' ('''\u0936\u093f\u0935 \u0917\u0902\u0917\u093e \u090f\u0915\u094d\u0938\u092a\u094d\u0930\u0947\u0938''') is a [[Superfast/Mail Trains in India|Superfast]] train of [[North Eastern Railway Zone]] named after the two jewels of [[Varanasi]]: [[Lord Shiva]] and the [[Ganges]] river. The main towns along the route are [[Prayagraj]] and [[Kanpur]].It was passed in 2002's [[Railway Budget]] and hence initiated its journey from 1 July 2002. It operates daily and covers a distance of {{convert|755|km|mi}} from [[Manduadih railway station|Manduadih]] to [[New Delhi railway station|New Delhi]]. Shiv Ganga Express originally consisted of 24 [[ICF Coaches]] which includes 1 First AC coach, 1 Second AC coach, 4 Third AC coach, 10 Sleeper Class coaches,5 General (Un-Reserved) coaches, Pantry Car and 2 SLR overall 24 coaches that makes it one of the longest trains in India. Shiv Ganga Express is usually hauled by a [[WAP 4]] or a [[WAP 7]] Locomotive from [[Manduadih railway station|Manduadih]] to [[New Delhi Railway Station|New Delhi]]. It is considered as the best train between [[New Delhi]] and [[Varanasi]]. It has got a maximum speed of {{convert|110|kph|mph}}. It is one of the few [[Superfast/Mail Trains in India|Superfast]] trains which pass through [[Manduadih-Madho Singh-Allahabad]] section. This train is now running with 22 [[LHB Coaches]] from 16 June 2015 which includes 1 First AC Coach (H1), 1 Second AC Coach (A1), 4 Third AC Coaches (B1-B4), 9 Sleeper Class Coaches (S1-S9), 4 General (Un-Reserved) Coaches, Pantry Car and 2 EOG (End-on Generator).\n\n== Gallery ==\n<gallery>\nFile:12560 Shiv Ganga Express - EOG.jpg|12560 Shiv Ganga Express \u2013 EOG\nFile:12560 Shiv Ganga Express - Sleeper Class coach with Prayagraj Kumbh 2019 decal.jpg|12560 Shiv Ganga Express - Sleeper Class coach with [[Prayagraj Kumbh 2019]] decal\nFile:12560 Shiv Ganga Express - Pantry Car coach with Prayagraj Kumbh 2019 decal.jpg|12560 Shiv Ganga Express - Pantry Car coach with [[Prayagraj Kumbh 2019]] decal\nFile:12560 Shiv Ganga Express - AC 3 tier coach with Prayagraj Kumbh 2019 decal.jpg|12560 Shiv Ganga Express - AC 3 tier coach with [[Prayagraj Kumbh 2019]] decal\nFile:12560 Shiv Ganga Express - AC 2 tier coach with Prayagraj Kumbh 2019 decal.jpg|12560 Shiv Ganga Express - AC 2 tier coach with [[Prayagraj Kumbh 2019]] decal\nFile:12560 Shiv Ganga Express - AC 1st Class coach with Prayagraj Kumbh 2019 decal.jpg|12560 Shiv Ganga Express - AC 1st Class coach with [[Prayagraj Kumbh 2019]] decal\nFile:12560 Shiv Ganga Express - EOG with Kanpur based WAP 4.jpg|12560 Shiv Ganga Express - EOG with [[Kanpur Central|Kanpur]] based [[WAP 4]]\n</gallery>\n\n==Time Table==\n<br />\n'''From Varanasi New Delhi it starts with Number 12559 and time table is as:\n<br/>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! S.No. !! Station !! Arrival !! Departure !! Halt (Min.) !! Day !! Elevation\n|-\n|1 || [[Manduadih railway station|Manduadih]]  || Starting Station || 19:55 || - || 1 || 80m\n|-\n| 2 || [[Allahabad Junction railway station|Allahabad]] || 22:20 || 22:30 || 10 || 1 || 100m\n|-\n| 3 || [[Kanpur Central]] || 01:05 || 01:13 || 8 || 2 || 129m\n|-\n| 4 || [[New Delhi railway station|New Delhi]] || 08:10 || Destination || - || 2 || 216m\n|}\n\n'''From New Delhi to Manduadih(Varanasi) it starts with Number 12560 and time table is as:\n<br />\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! S.No. !! Station !! Arrival !! Departure !! Halt (Min.) !! Day !! Elevation\n|-\n| 1 || [[New Delhi railway station|New Delhi]] || Starting Station || 18:55 || - || 1 || 216m\n|-\n| 2 || [[Kanpur Central]] || 01:00 || 01:05 || 5 || 2 || 129m\n|-\n| 3 || [[Allahabad Junction railway station|Allahabad]] || 03:50 || 04:00 || 10 || 2 || 100m\n|-\n| 4 || [[Manduadih railway station|Manduadih]] || 06:50 || Destination || - || 2 || 80m\n\n|}\n\n==Reservation==\nPeople have to take an advanced reservation ticket to travel in the train except for the General class.\nIt records a rush of passengers throughout the year in both peak as well as non-peak period.\nBecause of its time of departure and arrival, it runs fully packed, therefore it is considered as a [[VIP]] train or '''Purvanchal Rajdhani''' by [[Indian Railway]].\n\n==Coach composition==\n\nThis train has 22 coaches between Manduadih to New Delhi station.\n\n9 Sleeper class Coach (S1 to S9)<br>\n4 Sleeper 3 Tier AC Coach (B1 to B4)<br>\n1 1st Class AC Coach (H1)<br>\n1 AC 2 Tier Coach (A1)<br>\n4 General compartments (Unreserved)<br>\n1 Pantry Car<br>\n2 EOGs\n\nCoach composition for 12559 :\n\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders unsortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| Loco\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style=\"background:lightskyblue;\"| 1\n!scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"1\" style